Chadian troops killed 384 Libyans andcaptured 48 in fighting near the key Libyan air base of OuadiDoum in northern Chad, a Chadian government statement said.    The statement issued by Chad's Paris embassy saidgovernment troops had "completely annihilated" a Libyan columnyesterday some 45 km (28 miles) from the Libyan base.    It was the highest number of Libyan casualties reportedsince January 2, when Chadian troops overran an importantgarrison at the oasis of Fada with the loss of more than 700Libyan troops.    Ouadi Doumi, central northern Chad, is the site of Libya'smain airfield in the country and several clashes have beenreported over the past week in the surrounding desert betweentroops loyal to President Hissene Habre and Libyan forces. Reuter&#3;